title: Sketches from Fontainebleau
medium: Graphite on off-white wove paper tipped into binding with fabric
description: Vertical sheet with a variety of sketches: engaged columns, molding profiles, a scaled drawing of a fireplace elevation and a three-quarter view of a lighlyt rendered mansard roof buliding.  Possibly also at bottom left is part of a scaled wall elevation.  There are many inscriptions with dimenions of certain elements of the drawings.
name: Album page
